 shot in Himachal Pradesh]]\n[[Category:2003 directorial debut films]]\n", "name_user": "Gotitbro", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paap"}
{"title_page": "Brother's Keeper (2002 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2002 American television film by John Badham}}\n{{Infobox television \n| show_name = Brother's Keeper\n| image = \n| caption = \n| genre = Crime, drama\n| writer = [[Steven Baigelman]]<br>Glenn Gers\n| director = [[John Badham]]\n| starring = [[Jeanne Tripplehorn]]<br>[[Corin Nemec]]<br>[[Leland Orser]]\n| executive_producer =\n| producer = Justis Greene\n| location =  \n| music = [[John Ottman]]\n| cinematography = Ron Stannett\n| editor = [[Frank Morriss]]\n| company = [[New Line Television]]\n| distributor = \n| network = [[USA Network]]\n| released = January 29, 2002\n| runtime = 86 minutes\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| budget = \n}}\n\n'''''Brother's Keeper''''' is a 2002 American [[television film|made-for-television]] [[crime film|crime drama]] film directed by [[John Badham]] and written by [[Steven Baigelman]] and Glenn Gers. The film stars [[Jeanne Tripplehorn]] as a former police investigator drawn to a series of [[serial killer|serial killings]] in [[Portland, Oregon]] that may have been committed by her disturbed younger brother, played by [[Corin Nemec]].\n\n''Brother's Keeper'' was produced by [[New Line Television]] and filmed in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]], Canada. It aired in the United States on the [[USA Network]] on January 29, 2002.<ref name=\"variety1\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2002/tv/reviews/brother-s-keeper-2-1200551677/|title=Brother's Keeper|last=Fries|first=Laura|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=January 28, 2002|accessdate=April 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\nThe film began shooting in [[Vancouver]] on May 21, 2001. It was originally titled ''Breeders''.<ref name=\"variety2\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2001/tv/news/usa-an-original-player-1117797802/|title=USA an original player|last=Grego|first=Melissa|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 25, 2001|accessdate=April 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Jeanne Tripplehorn]] as Lucinda Pond\n* [[Corin Nemec]] as Ellis Pond\n* [[Leland Orser]] as Travis Adler\n* [[Evan Parke]] as Junior\n* Brian Jensen as David Pond\n* Ben Cardinal as Running Bear\n* [[Britt McKillip]] as Young Lucinda / Marie\n* [[Cameron Bright]] as Young Ellis\n* [[Andrew Jackson (actor)|Andrew Jackson]] as Adam\n* William S. Taylor as Tierney\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{IMDb title|id=0287944|title=Brother's Keeper}}\n\n{{John Badham}}\n\n[[Category:2002 films]]\n[[Category:2002 television films]]\n[[Category:American serial killer films]]\n[[Category:American crime drama films]]\n[[Category:Films about child abuse]]\n[[Category:Films about siblings]]\n[[Category:Films directed by John Badham]]\n[[Category:Films scored by John Ottman]]\n[[Category:Films set in Portland, Oregon]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Vancouver]]\n[[Category:Police detective films]]\n[[Category:USA Network original films]]\n[[Category:American drama television film stubs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television \n| show_name = Brother's Keeper\n| image = \n| caption = \n| genre = Crime, drama\n| writer = [[Steven Baigelman]]<br>Glenn Gers\n| director = [[John Badham]]\n| starring = [[Jeanne Tripplehorn]]<br>[[Corin Nemec]]<br>[[Leland Orser]]\n| executive_producer =\n| producer = Justis Greene\n| location =  \n| music = [[John Ottman]]\n| cinematography = Ron Stannett\n| editor = [[Frank Morriss]]\n| company = [[New Line Television]]\n| distributor = \n| network = [[USA Network]]\n| released = January 29, 2002\n| runtime = 86 minutes\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| budget = \n}}\n\n'''''Brother's Keeper''''' is a 2002 [[television film|made-for-television]] [[crime film|crime drama]] film directed by [[John Badham]] and written by [[Steven Baigelman]] and Glenn Gers. The film stars [[Jeanne Tripplehorn]] as a former police investigator drawn to a series of [[serial killer|serial killings]] in [[Portland, Oregon]] that may have been committed by her disturbed younger brother, played by [[Corin Nemec]].\n\n''Brother's Keeper'' was produced by [[New Line Television]] and filmed in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]], Canada. It aired in the United States on the [[USA Network]] on January 29, 2002.<ref name=\"variety1\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2002/tv/reviews/brother-s-keeper-2-1200551677/|title=Brother's Keeper|last=Fries|first=Laura|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=January 28, 2002|accessdate=April 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\nThe film began shooting in [[Vancouver]] on May 21, 2001. It was originally titled ''Breeders''.<ref name=\"variety2\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2001/tv/news/usa-an-original-player-1117797802/|title=USA an original player|last=Grego|first=Melissa|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 25, 2001|accessdate=April 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Jeanne Tripplehorn]] as Lucinda Pond\n* [[Corin Nemec]] as Ellis Pond\n* [[Leland Orser]] as Travis Adler\n* [[Evan Parke]] as Junior\n* Brian Jensen as David Pond\n* Ben Cardinal as Running Bear\n* [[Britt McKillip]] as Young Lucinda / Marie\n* [[Cameron Bright]] as Young Ellis\n* [[Andrew Jackson (actor)|Andrew Jackson]] as Adam\n* William S. Taylor as Tierney\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{IMDb title|id=0287944|title=Brother's Keeper}}\n\n{{John Badham}}\n\n[[Category:2002 films]]\n[[Category:2002 television films]]\n[[Category:American serial killer films]]\n[[Category:American crime drama films]]\n[[Category:Films about child abuse]]\n[[Category:Films about siblings]]\n[[Category:Films directed by John Badham]]\n[[Category:Films scored by John Ottman]]\n[[Category:Films set in Portland, Oregon]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Vancouver]]\n[[Category:Police detective films]]\n[[Category:USA Network original films]]\n[[Category:American drama television film stubs]]\n", "name_user": "DoubleCross", "label": "safe", "comment": "short description, country in lead", 